claim.claim-text:
1. A center beam rail road car comprising: 
a deck structure upon which lading can be supported, the deck structure being carried by spaced apart rail car trucks; 
a central beam structure running along the deck structure and extending upwardly therefrom; 
lading securement apparatus for restraining lading carried upon said deck structure; and 
lading securement storage apparatus mounted to said deck structure; 
said lading securement apparatus including 
at least one band of webbing for wrapping about the lading, 
securing equipment mounted to at least one of (a) said deck structure and (b) said central beam structure, by which to anchor said band of webbing to at least one of (a) said deck structure and (b) said central beam structure, 

lading securement storage apparatus including 
a winder mounted to said deck structure, said winder being operable to form said band into a storage configuration; 
an enclosure mounted to said deck structure, said enclosure having a storage space defined therein for accommodating the band of webbing; and 
said deck structure being free of obstruction by said winder and said enclosure when lading is carried by said deck structure.

14. The center beam rail road car of claim 1 wherein: 
said car has lading bunk envelopes defined above said deck structure and to either side of said central beam structure; 
said winder includes a crank; 
said enclosure has a pair of opposed walls having apertures formed therein to define a socket for receiving said crank in a position for winding said webbing; 
said enclosure is pivotally mounted to said deck structure, said enclosure being movable to a stored position clear of said lading bunk envelopes.

15. A rail road car comprising: 
a deck structure for supporting lading, said deck structure being supported on railcar trucks for rolling motion along railroad tracks; 
lading securement apparatus connected to said deck structure, said lading securement apparatus including at least one web band for wrapping about the lading and at least one tightening mechanism operable to draw the band tight about the lading to restrain the lading relative to the deck structure; 
a lading securement storage apparatus mounted to the deck structure, said lading securement storage apparatus including an enclosure mounted to said deck structure, said enclosure having an opening defined therein for admitting said web band to be placed within said enclosure; 
said enclosure being movable to a first position in which said opening is exposed to permit said web band to be introduced therein; and 
said enclosure being movable to a second position in which said opening is obstructed.

21. A center beam rail road car comprising: 
a deck structure carried upon spaced apart rail car trucks; 
a central beam assembly running along said deck structure and standing upwardly thereof, bunks for carrying lading being defined to either side of said central beam structure above said deck structure; 
said central beam structure having an array of posts standing upwardly of said deck structure; 
lading securement apparatus for securing lading in said bunks, said lading securement apparatus including web bands for wrapping about the lading; 
a storage enclosure mounted between a pair of said posts; and 
a winder mechanism mounted between a pair of said posts for reeling said bands; and 
a storage enclosure for accommodating wound web bands, said storage enclosure being mounted between a pair of said posts.
